},{"label":"Cash conversion","value":1.57,"unit":"\u00d7","status":"good","read":"1.57\u00d7 of profit came in as operating cash (5-yr median) \u2014 well backed.","meaning":"Median of (cash from operations \u00f7 net profit) over the last 5 years.","why_useful":"Profit you can't collect as cash is fragile; >0.8\u00d7 means earnings are real cash, <0.6\u00d7 is an accrual red flag.","why_it_can_fail":"One-off working-capital swings or a capex year can distort a single ratio; the 5-yr median smooths it."},{"label":"Balance-sheet safety","value":0.67,"unit":"\u00d7 D/E","status":"weak","read":"Leveraged (D/E 0.67\u00d7, interest cover 1.1\u00d7).","meaning":"Latest debt-to-equity and interest coverage (EBIT \u00f7 interest) from the balance sheet.","why_useful":"Low debt and high interest cover let a business survive a downturn; high debt amplifies trouble.","why_it_can_fail":"Off-balance-sheet leases/guarantees aren't captured; a cash-rich firm can show low D/E yet still be risky elsewhere."},{"label":"Earnings momentum","value":-48.67,"unit":"% YoY","status":"weak","read":"Profit down 49% YoY (latest TTM).","meaning":"Trailing-twelve-month net profit vs the year-ago TTM (and whether the YoY rate is rising = 'accelerating').","why_useful":"Improving, accelerating earnings tend to drive re-rating; falling profit warns of a deteriorating business.","why_it_can_fail":"TTM can be lumpy for cyclicals/one-offs; cross-check the multi-year trend on the Fundamentals tab."}]},"valuation":{"ok":true,"is_bank":false,"pe_now":40.0,"pe_percentile":94.0,"median_pe":31.1,"earnings_yield_pct":2.5,"pb":2.11,"ev_ebitda":12.42,"quality_score":57.0,"pat_cagr_5y_pct":8.1,"peg":4.94,"cheapness":{"status":"weak","read":"P/E at the 94-percentile of its 10-yr range \u2014 expensive vs its own history."},"expectations":"At 40.0\u00d7 earnings for ~8% 5-yr profit CAGR, the market is paying \u22484.94\u00d7 growth (PEG). >2 = a lot already priced in; <1 = cheap if growth holds. This PEG divides 